The paper proposes a solution using Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) in a multi-agent environment to address the problem of energy sharing in a Zero Energy Community (ZEC). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI, which deals with artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper also involves multiple agents interacting with each other, which suggests the category cs.MA (multi-agent systems). The problem of energy sharing in a ZEC involves control and optimization, which falls under the category cs.SY (systems and control). The use of DRL also suggests the category cs.LG (machine learning), which deals with deep learning and neural networks. Finally, the paper involves energy and sustainability, which could fall under the category cs.ET (emerging technologies).
